==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|melten|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|meltan||to consume by fire, melt, burn up; dissolve, digest|lang=ang}} and {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|mieltan||to melt; digest; refine, purge; exhaust|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*meltaną||to dissolve, melt}} and {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*maltijaną||to dissolve, melt}}, both from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*(s)mel-||to beat, crush, grind}}. Cognate with {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|melta||to melt, digest|lang=is}}.

